      "span_text": "On stable coastlines, a simple model would suggest that marine terraces or reefs will be left as emergent records only during times that sea level is higher-and therefore global ice volume is lowerthan present. This concept is complicated, however, by glaciohydro-isostatic contributions to sea level, i.e., deformation of the Earth's surface associated with the growth and decay of large ice sheets [CITATION_1] )."
